title: How to make Thunderbird open with the same pane layout regardless of how it was when I closed it
creator: cjholly
content: I need predictability where I can find it. Thunderbird opens how I left it, so I never know what's going to appear when I start it the next day. Isn't there some setting so that it always opens showing all 3 panes, regardless of my laziness at exit? It would also help with my autohotkey script if it knew what to expect. I suspect the lack of answers in my search suggests there is no such setting. How about a command line argument?

title: Bulk‑deleting messages I manually marked as Junk in Thunderbird 147.0.2
creator: shersted
content: I’m running Thunderbird 147.0.2 (64‑bit) on Windows. In this version, there is no Mail Toolbar and no Junk/Spam button available in the Unified Toolbar layout. My issue is this: When I manually mark messages as Junk, they stay in the folder where I marked them. They do not automatically move to the Junk folder, and there is no way to bulk‑delete or bulk‑move the messages I personally marked as Junk. I’m trying to find out: - Is there a built‑in way in Thunderbird 147 to bulk‑delete messages that I manually marked as Junk? - If not, is this a known limitation of the new interface? - Is there a recommended workflow for users who manually mark spam but do not have the classic Mail Toolbar? I’m not looking to switch to the Classic interface — I just want to know how to manage manually‑marked junk in bulk in the current Unified Toolbar layout. Thanks for any guidance.

title: Profile file size
creator: dog3
content: I'd like to reduce the size of my profile file xxxxxx.default . it is currently 17.2 GB. If I delete several of the folders in the "Local Folder" (example "sent mail 2010"), will the file size shrink or does it only expand to fit the folders.

title: Data Breach warning - is it correct?
creator: malc.crawford
content: I've just received an email from breach-alerts@mozilla.com stating: You’ve been in a new data breach. Breach source: CarGurus. Yet there's no record of CarGurus in the Mozilla Monitor database. Is this an erroneous message? Or have I missed something obvious? Thanks

title: Blue highlights on new message
creator: shersted
content:
In my current version of Thunderbird, new messages show a dark blue subject line only until I click on them. After I open the message once, the blue highlight disappears. Is this the normal behavior now?

Is there any way to extend that same dark‑blue highlight to other emails as its really helpful to provide good contrast between individual emails.

Thanks, Steve

title: Hello, I just switched to Starlink and today tried to send an email and it was rejected by the smtp email server timed out. Trying to find the smtp server any suggestions.
creator: rwillbanksis
content: Hello, I have tried to send several email replies using thunder bird but they fail because the smtp server times out. Or cannot be reached. I am a new Starlink subscriber and am wondering if that could have anything to do with the issues. The software is on my dell computer running windows 10. Any help or suggestion is appreciated. Buoyantly Professor Bob

creator: ashuat
content: Hi, since Eudora doesn't work anymore, I'm trying Thunderbir, so I transferred the emails with "ImportExport Tool". The emails that are transferred from Eudora to Thunderbird are mixed up with the ones I deleted.I'll give you an example: if I get some propaganda email, I delete them as well as the messages that come from the forums that say: there's a response to your post.In fact, the messages transferred are too many, 2500. And only those messages that I had deleted do not have the subject, but only the title. So I have a lot of confusion of messages.In "ImportExport Tool" I used "Import individual mbox files". What does "Import individual mbox files with sbd structure" mean? I hope I have chosen the right option for importing emails. Maybe I need to configure "ImportExport Tool"? Thank you.

title: E-Mails über Thunderbird geht seit gestern nicht mehr zu versenden
creator: elisabeth.gulich
content:
Hi, ich nutze für meine Mails t-online über Thunderbird. Seit gestern kann ich von meinem Laptop auf diesem Wege keine Mail mehr versenden. (Der Eingang funktioniert aber einwandfrei, ich erhalte alle Mails.)

Es erscheint jedes Mal die folgende Meldung, wenn ich eine E-Mail geschrieben habe und auf Senden klicke: Senden der Nachricht fehlgeschlagen. "Fehler beim Senden der Nachricht: SMTP-Server-Fehler. Der Mail-Server antwortete: IP=38.246.32.9 - Your address is blocked.

Vom Handy aus kann ich E-mails reibungslos versenden, vom E-Mail-Center der Telekom aus funktioniert das auch. Ich habe weder Passwörter noch sonstige Zugangsdaten verändert. Die Einstellungen im E-Mail-Center finden Sie im Anhang.

Woran kann es liegen? Schon mal vielen Dank. Elisabeth

title: Lost Emails in Inbox
creator: christophleib
content:
Hello, so finally this happens to me too. I lost all my emails in Inbox before August 2025. I think it happened after one of these usual alerts 'you should compress emails'. I did this in the past 6, 7 years and nothing was lost so far. I also have plenty of space on my computer, that's not a thing. I tried a couple things I found in web but doesn't help. Couple emails that I had for example in an 'important' folder are still there. I'm really annoyed. I didn't had a glue at all that this compression alert will delete files in the inbox one day, only those in the trash box. Maybe there is a last chance to get them back but I'm afraid that they are gone forever and I will put everything from my inbox into an other folder in future or maybe even better go back to Apple Email where this never ever happened in the past 25 years.

Thank you, Chris

title: Thunderbird and Firefox overlap hided taskbar
creator: bogdan
content:
Hi

When Thunderbird is started in full screen it overlap taskbar if is set to hide and taskbar won't show until Thunderbird is minimized and maximized. Another way is to press the Win key two times. Then the hided taskbar can be shown/use. The same thing happens to Firefox. Only when is first started. Then if Firefox is minimized and maximized, press Win key two times, press F11 two times then the hided taskbar show/hide normal.

It is a setting that can be changed to start Thunderbird and Firefox in full screen and do not overlap hided taskbar?

title: Thunderbird failing to login to BT email
creator: coopern1
content: Thunderbird now consistently fails on attempting to login to BT email. It worked fine one day and not the next. It now fails every time. It now just says "Host contacted - sending login information", then comes up with an error "Sending of password did not succeed". Nothing has been changed - no settings, nothing. I had not been anywhere near the setting but have now examined them and they are indeed exactly as they were and, having checked, are exactly as they are supposed to be. The saved username and password are as they should be and I am able to login to BT email on a browser using those credentials and send and receive email with no problems. It therefore appears that there is no issue at BT and the account has not been blocked due to too many login attempts. I have cleared cache, deleted and re-installed Thunderbird but it makes no difference. Are there any ideas as to how to fix this?
